# Price Data Rules

- Never call external price APIs directly from client components.
- Always go through the `/api/prices` route handler.
- Price data is cached server-side with 24-hour TTL (`lib/prices/cache.ts`).
- Use `lib/formatters.ts` for all currency display — never raw `.toString()`.
- Always include `updatedAt` in price displays so users know data freshness.
- Fallback prices exist in `lib/prices/constants.ts` for when APIs are unavailable.
- Show a warning banner in Arabic when using fallback/stale data.
